      "charStart": 864,
      "factId": "hz.web.449627d44882ccf7.fact.4",
      "kind": "bullet",
      "text": "The talk explains the method behind how this works, and then in a number of steps, develops firstly a grammar that requires a general parser such as ixml's to verify credit card numbers, and then uses that to generate an LL1 grammar working left-to-right that achieves the same purpose.",
